Document: Your Second 3D Shader
Path: godot/tutorials/shaders/your_first_shader/your_second_3d_shader.rst
Summary: This document introduces the creation of a second 3D shader in Godot, building upon the concepts of the first.

This tutorial will guide you through creating your second 3D shader in Godot. We'll expand on the basic principles introduced previously and explore more advanced techniques to enhance your visual effects.

We will cover:
*   Understanding the shader editor interface for 3D shaders.
*   Exploring common shader types and their applications in 3D.
*   Writing a simple spatial shader from scratch.
*   Using uniforms to control shader parameters from the editor.
*   Implementing basic lighting interactions.
*   Applying the shader to a 3D mesh in your scene.

Let's begin by opening the shader editor and creating a new spatial shader resource.
